    "Body": " Posted by: Melinda Norris, SHRM-CP Melinda Norris, SHRM-CP Talent Acquisition Specialist at Voice Get to Know Voice Voice is a rewards-based social media network for content creation, discovery and discussion. Built by and for its users, Voice aims to rebuild public trust in media by focusing on transparency, authenticity, and alignment.?? Spun out of Block.One and built on the EOSIO protocol, Voice leverages the inherent characteristics of blockchain technology to architect integrity into the platform. Our team is looking for a passionate UX Researcher to investigate, test, analyze and inform solutions for building innovative and engaging features within Voice. Be part of a flat, agile work environment that values work/life balance. The ideal candidate will not only have a broad understanding of human factors, user-centric design practices and modern UX conventions, but can also collaborate with product teams to understand underlying requirements creating easy, delightful experiences for users. You will work closely with the UX team, product managers, engineers, and users to help identify business needs and articulate effective solutions based on complex data sets and best usability practices. You will generate usability test plans, process flows, and produce reports that you will present directly to stakeholders. You will generate wireframes and prototypes in conjunction with designers, and work closely with development teams to drive and conduct usability testing. You will lead usability research efforts across various products, and act as the user advocate throughout the entire software development lifecycle. Responsibilities Develop research plans, recommending specific methodologies as appropriate Design questionnaires, discussion guides and surveys for use in conducting research Execute or facilitate research, including questionnaire/interview guide development and/or moderating/facilitating sessions Analyze results/data and translate into clear and useful strategic and tactical insights to support stakeholders and project teams Translate concepts and research into user flows, wireframes, mockups and prototypes that lead to intuitive user experiences. Facilitate the product vision by researching, conceiving, sketching, prototyping and user-testing experiences for digital products. Deliver wireframes, user stories, user journeys, and mockups optimized for a wide range of devices and interfaces. Identify usability problems and devise elegant solutions. Make strategic design and user-experience decisions related to core, and new, features. Collaborate with other team members and stakeholders. Push to research, discover and explore new innovative techniques and methods for design and usability. Cooperate with developers to match visual design and user experience intent Contribute to overall Design Team processes and libraries. ?? Qualifications 3+ years of experience conducting customer and product research, including study design, moderating/facilitating, analysis, and requisite software/hardware tools. Preference will be given to candidates who have experience researching/designing complex solutions for complete digital environments. Experience with executing or facilitating research, analyzing results/data and translating into a clear and useful strategic insight to support stakeholders and project teams. Ability to convey complex, technical subject matter in a clear and straightforward manner Experience with qualitative and quantitative analytical techniques and tools?? Experience with web analytics tools, customer experience tools, and/or marketing research tools Comprehensive understanding of usability practices and principles applicable to user-centered design. Expertise in UX software such as Sketch, InVision, UXPin, Framer, or Marvel App. Basic React, SCSS, or JavaScript skills are a plus. Experience with the Adobe Creative Suite - specifically Adobe XD & Illustrator is preferred. "
